      <h1 class="center">Presentation Guideline</h1>

      <h2 class="col l5 m5 s12">Platform Presentation</h2>
      <ul class="col offset-l1 l6 m6 s12">

	<li>All platform presenters will have a slot (approximately 15 min
	  presentation) in the program.</li>
	
	<li>It is recommended to use the <a href='/ppt_template.pptx' download>presentation template</a> but not required.</li>
	<li>
	  Your talk will have <strong>15 minutes strictly </strong>and 3 min for Q&amp;A. We suggest that your
	  presentation should have 10 to 15 slides in total.
	</li>
	<li>
Arrive in session room <strong>at least 15 minutes before the start of your session</strong> to introduce
yourself to the session chair.
	</li>
	<li>
	  You are requested to load your presentation in a USB stick onto the laptop in your
	  presentation room in advance of your session (<strong>at least half a day prior to your scheduled
	  session</strong>). Rooms are indicated on the conference program. You will not be permitted to use
	  your laptop or Mac computer for your talk but should load it onto the laptop in your
	  meeting room. Each session will have a named folder on the desktop.
	</li>
	<li>
The operating system on all computers at the conference will be windows 10 professional
and running office 2016. All presentations should be in PowerPoint only that is compatible
with this operating system.
	</li>
	<li>
	  Be sure to test your presentation in the Speaker Ready Room before uploading your
	  presentation.
	</li>

	<li>
	  Please send us your short bio (education, research areas) by <strong>August 4</strong>.
	  </li>


      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
    <h2 class="col l5 m5 s12">Poster Presentation</h2>

    <ul class="col offset-l1 l6 m6 s12">
      <li>All poster presenters will have a place at the venue to display their
	poster. Poster presenters need to print their own poster and bring it to
	the conference, <strong>the poster size must be 80 cm wide by 120 cm long.</strong>
	
	It is recommended to use the standard <a href='/poster_template.ppt' download>poster template</a> but not required. </li>

      <li>
	You can use <strong>pins only</strong> (no velcro or tape) to put up their posters.
      </li>
      <li>
	You may put up their poster on your assigned poster panel <strong>from 9 am onwards on August
	14, Monday.</strong>
      </li>
      <li>
	Poster session is scheduled on <strong>August 14, Monday from 4:00 â€“ 5:00 pm</strong>. Please be present
beside your poster during the session to explain your poster to delegates who will be
	viewing the posters.
      </li>
      <li>
	You may remove your posters from the poster boards <strong>after 5 pm on August 14, Monday</strong>. All
	the poster should be removed <strong>by 6 pm on the day</strong>. Any poster left after this time will be
	disposed.
      </li>
    </ul>

